<TITLE> Water fells 300 factory workers in Savar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, August 1 (bdnews24.com)  Around 300 employees of PGCL Garments in Ashulia reported sick on Saturday after drinking the supply water, just days after an outbreak of food poisoning at the same factory, which left more than 500 workers ill. "Around 300 workers became ill at around 10 in the morning after drinking the factory's supply water. They started vomiting and also had diarrhoea," a factory employee, not wanting to be named, told bdnews24.com. Many of the employees had to be admitted to local hospitals and clinics, said Monowar Hossain, officer-in-charge of Ashulia Police Station. Police were stationed outside the building when relatives of the employees started gathered at the factory gate. Officials at PGCL Garments said they were investigating the matter. bdnews24.
